This rib re-expresses the Chamber multi-agent desktop app as a Keelson rib. It
imports none of the upstream code: its genesis, room, and lens machinery is a
clean-room port of the concepts below onto the `Rib` contract. Attribution to
the upstream project whose vision this rib builds on follows.

==============================================================================
Concepts from: Chamber (minds, lenses, genesis, A2A rooms)
==============================================================================

The rib's multi-agent model — persistent "minds" authored on demand (genesis),
agent-to-agent "rooms," and agent-authored "lenses" rendered through the canvas
— is ported from Chamber, the originating multi-agent desktop app by Ian
Philpot, used under the MIT License. The strategies and orchestration are
re-typed for Keelson and driven by the `Rib` contract; nothing is imported.

  Project: Chamber
  Source:  https://github.com/ianphil/chamber
